column5: Took a drive up to the cottage on the north end of Pigeon.  No damage and only small branches down.  Trees pretty bare now.  Water levels down 2 inches in a week even with the rain, and gin clear.
The storm was pretty much a bust throughout the Kawarthas, thankfully.
I'm hoping mine is the same up near Parry Sound...we just sold it, closing in 30 days. Last thing i need is a giant tree in the living room!

Im hoping the same, im in the same area.  If anyone from Sprucedale to Parry sound knows, please report.  I have a couple of bad trees that were slated to come down in spring, maybe mother nature took care of them.

One of the guys stayed up Sunday night to clean out the fridges and shut down the cottage for the winter. He's still "trapped" there, although he admitted he got out to Sans Souci for provisions" yesterday, LOL
